messages.content: Haha it's a really good book
Wow thatâs a lot of chapters. No matter how many times you read Harry Potter, itâs not enough.

Haha great! I have some friends who I think have read the Harry Potter books 10 times. I just started reading a comic book story called Tower of God. I would recommend it - you can read it online. But if you do, make sure you start at the beginning - there's over 400 chapters.
I could try. Can you believe Iâm reading Harry Potter again. The 4th part? I still love reading
So do you still love to read?

It was called the Upward Bound Program. The classes were in Arrak, but most of the students were from town. I think Handy Emil was the only one from Laura. If you are ever back in Majuro during the summer, you could be a tutor or resident assistant for Upward Bound - they pay pretty good.
Aha yeah since we only have 2 hospitals back home. Where did you teach summer school at?
That's a good plan. I hope you do well in your medical assistant program - the Majuro hospital will be lucky to have you, if that's where you decide to work
Well Iâm pretty busy with school and everything. I want to at least have a certificate or a degree before I go back home and stay there for good.
I think I will go this summer to teach summer school again. Maybe I will stay longer than just the summer - I don't know. What about you?
Aha wow. I wish I could go visit them all. Yes I am still living with my grandma. Are you planning to go back anytime soon?
And visiting Laura was good - quite a few people have left for America. But I saw Roline and Waju and Neirose and Eugene and a bunch of other old LHS students. It was fun!
That's fantastic. That would be a great job! Are you still living with your Grandma?
My trade is Medical Administrative Assistant

Yes I am still in California, wanting to go back to my island ahah. Itâs good youâre still teaching. How are the people back home? Youâre not teaching Biology anymore? My English has gotten so much better right now. Iâm attending Job Corps
What about you? Are you still living in California?
Diana! Good to hear from you! I'm doing good - I'm teaching math in the state of Indiana. But this summer I was back in Laura teaching summer school.
Hi Andy, it's been so long. How are you doing?
And if i take that SAT and fail it again, then i will take it again and again. I just have to look for someone who can help me with tutoring and stuff.
I will take one again until my scores are great! I just have to get to know my school and the teachers in it first. I need to be prepared this time.

Those are pretty bad. I think you would do a lot better if you took it again sometime. You're a lot smarter than that score. We didn't really do that good a job of preparing in the Marshall Islands. And, you still did better than about 150,000 people
They're pretty bad uh?
Mr. Andy... Here are my SAT test score. 330-critical reading. 400-mathematic. 380-Writing
Cool. They don't have a BNJ church there? I gotta go somewhere in a minute, but keep me in on how you're doing, especially how you like your new school. Take care
There are so plenty of Marshallese there
There are some Marshallese here. And I also go to the um... Mormon Church
That's too bad. Maybe you can find a friendly church. Black people churches are known for being really friendly. Are there many Marshallese, besides your grandma?

No! The people here are so rude! They never said hi to one another. We only get to talk to the Marshallese people because we're afraid to talk to the people around here. And our neighborhood is full of black people. But I am trying to get used to their way of life.
Yeah, you should definitely try to go to  lots of parks and lakes. California is very beautiful. Do you have nice neighbors?

Oh ahaha no... I spent a week in Hawaii and then came here. It's so different here than back home. And also we don't get to go wherever we want here. It's also boring here,unlike the fun back home. The only thing I'm excited about being here is the schools that I will go to. And also the parks and lakes we also went to.
Awesome! Keep me up on how you like it there, if you have time. Were you in Hawaii for the last month?
I'm in Sacramento!
Surf? Ahaha no way... I might drown
OK. Good luck in Sacramento and God bless. Have fun in Hawaii; maybe you can learn how to surf
I don't know maybe... My grandmother is there
I know - lots of homeless people in Hawaii. So are there other Marshallese in Sacramento? Is that where Raymee moved to?
Very!... Here in hawaii I got to see mountains and hotels and restaurants and shops and many people... even the homeless ones
Are you excited to live in US?
Moving there!
For the summer, or are you moving there?
Just staying for a few days and then we will go to Sacramento this friday...
Cool! What are you doing in Hawaii?
Mr.Andy I'm in Hawaii right now and it's sooooo amazing
Ahahha okay;) Um I don't know what my score for the SAT was... I wish I did

Diana, I've been looking at some college scholarships that maybe you could apply for. Do you know what your score was for the SAT? Have you thought about taking it again? That might help you if you do really want to go to a U.S. college. Hope you're doing well. Make sure 11a looks sharp for the WASC people when they come
Ahahha that'll be great! Thanks

You're welcome, Diana. That's great that you're starting your own library; I think you would be a good librarian. I hope you like the books. Enjoy. If I send more books, I'll send some picture books too.

Ahahah Mr. Andrew did gave me the books Mr. Andy, and they're great! Thanks... I made a little library of mine as soon as I got them and some of my friends came and sign out books with me... I didn't know that being a librarian is what I also want to be in the future... Thanks again for the books Mr. Andy. I'm also trying to teach my young cousins and my younger brother how to read, but the books are too hard for them so I had to go look for children's books at the library and with someone who has children's books... Thanks a million times Mr.Andy... Thank you
Ahahah yes! Thank you... I'll be happy to share them with anyone who wants to read:) ur the best Mr.Andyð

Diana, I'm gonna send some books out there to Mr. Andrew. I think I'll tell him to give them to you, and then you can share them with other people. I'll try to pick good ones, but let me know if there's a certain book you want.
Please do... Thanks Mr.Andy... Ur the greatest! Thanks for everything though...
'll let you know if I hear of any others that might work for you.

Oh, alright. I really thought they would want you at the interview again this year. But if you do really want to go to college in the US or maybe somewhere else, there might be other scholarships you could get. I
Um... Actually I didn't go to the interview... Maybe next year... Thanks anyway for asking:)
Diana, how did the UWC scholarship interview go? Have you heard back from them yet?
U got it Mr. Scientistó¾
I will; she'll like that. And don't actually treat the scholarship like a contest; just try to have fun and get to know the other candidates. Take care. Bye!

Ehe... Don't worry... I'll try my best not to get nervous again. Thanks again for ur help last year... U were the best teacher ever... Say hello to ur sister Crista for me... Haven't forgotten her... Bye!
Cool. Good luck if you go to the interview again. Don't let any more Co-op students get this scholarship
Scared??! Ahahahha. I haven't heard from them yet... Maybe on Dec. 09.
Awesome! I knew it was happening about now, but I was scared to ask; you told me you would maybe apply. Have you heard back from them yet?
Ahahah I'm fine thank you. I just wanted to tell u that I applied to the UWC scholarship again... And also thanks for helping me with the one last yearó¾µ
Yeah. Kevin Harkey was telling me some people I could maybe stay with in Springdale. How are you?
Mr. And ur on facebook now??!!!
Thank you million timesó¾µ
